    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for the Senior Dev Role – Thank You\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to take a moment to express our gratitude for the time and effort you invested in the interview process for the Senior Dev role here in Austin. Your enthusiasm, technical prowess, and genuine interest in our team were truly commendable.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate who has a slightly more extensive background with our specific cloud architecture. This decision was not easy, as we were impressed by your skills and potential. We understand that this news may be disappointing, and we want to assure you that this decision does not reflect your abilities or potential. We were genuinely impressed by your talent and would love to keep the door open for future opportunities. Please feel free to reach out if you have any questions or if there's anything else we can assist you with.\n\nWe wanted to add a personal note to let you know how much we appreciated your time and the effort you put into the process. It was a difficult decision for our team, as we were torn between your impressive skills and the specific experience of the other candidate. We hope you understand that this was a tough call for us, and we truly regret any",
